<br>
I wasn't trying to open a debate about the existence or non-existence of God. I was making a point moreso about the convictions a Christian may feel when telling about God (originally). A Christian proclaims he does indeed feel he has the spirit of God in him...and it is that spirit that motivates him to spread the Word.<br>
<br>
The debate rages around the &quot;x-factor&quot;. The &quot;x&quot; is the existence or non-existence of God.<br>
<br>
Its really crazy how we still debate it so heavily today. I mean, the argument is &quot;Im atheist cause you cannot prove to me there is a God...so go away&quot;... vs. &quot;You cannot prove there isnt so listen..&quot;<br>
